                    <span>Purchased the book at Monticello during a visit to the east coast. For the rest of my vacation I couldn't put it down. I learned so much about the founding of our nation that was never tought to me in school.  Some of the things I was taught in school were down right wrong when compared to the actual words of the people who were there.  Jefferson is an amazing man and Adams provides comic relief against Jeffersons hard exterior. Great read!</span>
                  
              
